definitions.definition: To speak with a spasmodic repetition of vocal sounds ; to stammer , to stutter ; also, to mumble and procrastinate in one's speech ; to hem and haw .

main_definition: ( intransitive , chiefly British , dialectal , archaic ) To speak with a spasmodic repetition of vocal sounds ; to stammer , to stutter ; also, to mumble and procrastinate in one's speech ; to hem and haw .
